{
  "stem": "27340.5",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And I remember we were doing some unarmed combat when suddenly there was quite some noise, and the doors were being pushed open, broken open.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And there were some officials, I think in civilian clothes-- yes.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "It was obvious that they were Scotland Yard or some sort of police.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And I made-- I made a very quick escape through the window, but the window was on ground level.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "I didn't dive, you know, from the first or second or fourth floor, and I managed to get the away.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And I think they were fundamentally interested in not arresting anybody but just making sure that these sort of things would not go on that were obviously against the interests of the government.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "This must been early in 1948, possibly in February or March.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Exact dates I really don't know.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I mean, that happened throughout the-- the whole time.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You see, the Sochnut, the leadership of the Jewish community in Palestine, known as the Sochnut, consisted of people like Ben-Gurion.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Moshe Shertok, as he was named.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Later on, he changed his name to Sharett, became foreign minister.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Golda Meir, Berl Katznelson, very, very prominent people.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And in all their negotiations, they had to come to London because that is where the government, which was, after all, in charge of the mandate in Palestine, was situated.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And every time these people were here in London, the word used to come around through all the youth leaders, of whom I was one-- and there were about 16 or 17 of us in London-- and the old man is at the [?",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Bayit, ?] and the [?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Bayit ?] was, in fact, the headquarters, or was a hostel, a Habonim hostel, somewhere in East London, in Clapton, I think.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
